/* :is()

The :is() CSS pseudo-class funtion takes a selector list as its argument, and selects any element that can be selected by one of the selectors in that list

write less code */

/* nav h2:hover,
header h2:hover,
section h2:hover {
  color: red;
} */

:is(nav, header, ) h2:hover {
  color: red;
}
